09/07/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The fifth Croatia Summit opens on Friday (July 9th) in Dubrovnik. The two-day conference will bring together prime ministers and foreign ministers from the region, as well as European officials and representatives of international organisations. The main topic is facing global challenges. Serbia will not be represented due to Kosovo Prime Minister Hashim Thaci's attendance at the event. (Beta, RTRS, HRT, Vjesnik - 08/07/10) 
